(modified from Fluke 1945 , Thompson and Skevington 2014 ). Male dichoptic. Both sexes with face slightly receding to perpendicular with a well-rounded tubercle, facial pollinosity yellowish (broadly punctuate in the
Platycheirus stegnus
species group or Carposcalis subgenus as well as some Argentinomyia species), never with transversal grooves dorsally along tubercle (present in some
Argentinomyia
